'''Mouhamadou Habib Mbacke Diarra''' (born 3 January 2004) is a French-Senegalese professional [[Association football|footballer]] who plays as a [[midfielder]] for {{English football updater|Sunderld}} club [[Sunderland A.F.C.|Sunderland]] and the [[Senegal national football team|Senegal national team]].

==Club career==
===Strasbourg===
A youth product of [[FC Mulhouse|Mulhouse]] and [[RC Strasbourg Alsace|Strasbourg]], Diarra signed his first professional contract with Strasbourg on 18 August 2021.<ref name="auto">{{Cite web|url=https://www.rcstrasbourgalsace.fr/premier-contrat-pro-pour-habib-diarra-et-mahamadou-kanoute/|title=Premier contrat pro pour Habib Diarra et Mahamadou Kanouté|date=18 August 2021 }}</ref> He made his professional debut with Strasbourg in a 5–1 [[Ligue 1]] win over [[AS Saint-Étienne|Saint-Étienne]] on 17 October 2021.<ref>{{Cite web|url=https://int.soccerway.com/matches/2021/10/17/france/ligue-1/racing-club-de-strasbourg/association-sportive-de-saint-etienne-loire/3526000/|title=Strasbourg vs. Saint-Etienne - 17 October 2021 - Soccerway|website=int.soccerway.com}}</ref>

On July 21, 2022, Diarra extended his contract with Racing until June 2027.<ref>{{cite web|date=21 July 2022 |title=HABIB DIARRA PROLONGE JUSQU'EN 2027 |url=https://www.rcstrasbourgalsace.fr/habib-diarra-prolonge-jusquen-2027/ |website=www.rcstrasbourgalsace.fr}}<!-- auto-translated from French by Module:CS1 translator --></ref><ref>{{cite web|date=22 July 2022 |title=Habib Diarra signe pour deux ans de plus avec le Racing Club de Strasbourg Alsace |url=https://www.francebleu.fr/sports/football/habib-diarra-signe-pour-deux-ans-de-plus-avec-le-racing-club-de-strasbourg-alsace-1658483295 |website=www.francebleu.fr}}<!-- auto-translated from French by Module:CS1 translator --></ref>

On April 16, 2023, Diarra scored his first professional goal in Ligue 1 during the 31st matchday of the 2022–23 season, finding the net in the 71st minute against [[AC Ajaccio]], less than ten minutes after coming on as a substitute.

On November 23, 2023, Strasbourg announced a one-year extension of Diarra's contract, which now runs until June 2028.<ref>{{cite news |author=C. O.-B. |date=23 November 2023 |newspaper=[[L'Équipe]] |title=Habib Diarra prolonge jusqu'en 2028 avec Strasbourg |language=fr|url=https://www.lequipe.fr/Football/Actualites/Habib-diarra-prolonge-jusqu-en-2028-avec-strasbourg/1433115 |url-access=subscription}}</ref>

===Sunderland===
On 1 July 2025, Diarra moved to [[Premier League]] side [[Sunderland A.F.C.|Sunderland]], signing a five-year contract.<ref>{{Cite web |title=Habib Diarra signs for Sunderland |url=https://www.safc.com/news/2025/july/01/diarra-arrives-on-wearside/ |access-date=2025-07-01 |website=www.safc.com}}</ref>

==International career==
Born in Senegal, Diarra moved to France at a young age. He was a youth international for France, having represented the [[France national under-16 football team|France U16]]s and [[France national under-18 football team|U18]]s.<ref name="auto"/> In March 2024, Diarra accepted a call-up from [[Aliou Cissé]], thereby transferring to [[Senegal]].<ref>{{cite news |title=ALIOU CISSÉ CONVINCES STRASBOURG'S HABIB DIARRA TO REJECT FRANCE SELECTION FOR SENEGAL |url=https://www.getfootballnewsfrance.com/2024/aliou-cisse-convinces-strasbourgs-habib-diarra-to-reject-france-selection-for-senegal/ |access-date=21 March 2024 |work=Get Football France |date=14 March 2024}}</ref>

He made his debut for the senior [[Senegal national football team|Senegal national team]] on 22 March 2024 in a friendly against [[Gabon national football team|Gabon]].<ref>{{cite web|publisher=ESPN|url=https://www.espn.co.uk/football/match/_/gameId/699778/gabon-senegal|title=Senegal v Gabon game report|date=22 March 2024}}</ref>

In January 2026, following Senegal's victory at the [[2025 Africa Cup of Nations]], he was received by the mayor of [[Mulhouse]].<ref>{{cite web|access-date=2026-01-27 |language=FR-fr |title=Vainqueur de la Coupe d'Afrique des Nations, Habib Diarra reçoit un accueil triomphal à Mulhouse |url=https://www.lalsace.fr/videos/vainqueur-de-la-coupe-d-afrique-des-nations-habib-diarra-recoit-un-accueil-triomphal-a-mulhouse-35zqmsz |website=www.lalsace.fr}}<!-- auto-translated from French by Module:CS1 translator --></ref>

